cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CR

This paper deals with reasoning on knowledge bases with defeasible axioms, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. The use of datalog and answer set semantics also suggests a connection to logic and databases, which are covered by cs.LO and cs.DB respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of textual information, which falls under the scope of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the study of exceptions and defeasibility in reasoning can also be relevant to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
